canonical:
  title: 賀正朝表
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 寅回斗柄聿更鳳曆之端春滿椒觴茂衍龍墀之慶懽聲競沸瑞氣旁流欽惟剛健粹精聦明睿智建皇極而大一統克綏萬邦欽昊天而定四時以凝庶績今辰方届於泰長多福益臻於鼎新伏念臣幸際昌時叨承異渥迹雖阻於漢殿未獲趨蹌心竊效於堯封倍申頌祝
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀正朝表
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 寅回斗柄。聿更鳳曆之端。春滿椒觴。茂衍龍墀之慶。懽聲競沸。瑞氣旁流。欽惟剛健粹精。聦明睿智。建皇極而大一統。克綏萬邦。欽昊天而定四時。以凝庶績。今辰方届於泰長。多福益臻於鼎新。伏念臣幸際昌時。叨承異渥。迹雖阻於漢殿。未獲趨蹌。心竊效於堯封。倍申頌祝。
korean:
  title: 하 정조 표
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 두병(斗柄)이 인(寅)으로 돌아와 다시 봉력(鳳曆)의 시초가 되고, 초상(椒觴)에 봄이 가득하여 용치(龍墀)의 경사가 성대히 거행되오니, 환성이 다투어 들끓고 서기(瑞氣)가 넘쳐 흐르옵나이다. 공경히 생각하옵건대, 강건(剛健)ㆍ수정(粹精)하옵시고, 총명ㆍ예지하시어 황극(皇極)을 세우고 일통(一統)을 크게 하여 바로 만방(萬邦)을 편안케 하시고, 하늘을 공경하고 사시(四時)를 정하여 서적(庶績)을 든든하게 하시었으니 이제 때가 바야흐로 태장(泰長)에 다다라 많은 복이 더욱 새롭게 이르리이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 신(臣)이 다행히 성대(盛代)를 만나 외람되이 남다른 은혜를 입었사옵기 몸은 비록 한전(漢殿)에 나아가 추창(趨蹌)하지 못하오나, 마음은 그윽이 요봉(堯封)을 본닫아 곱절로 송축(頌祝)을 드리옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0670&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Presenting Felicitations for the New Year
  author: Byeon Gyeyangʻ
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The Great Bear's handle returns to the east,
    Heralding anew the Phoenix Calendar's dawn.
    Spring brims in the pepper wine cup,
    As dragon-steps of fortune manifest in splendor.
    Joyous voices compete in exultation,
    Auspicious vapor flows and overflowing.

    I humbly reflect: strong and pure in essence,
    Clear in mind and wise in judgment—
    You have raised the imperial standard and achieved great unity,
    Bringing peace to all nations under heaven.
    Honoring the sky, you set the seasons in their course,
    Consolidating the achievements of all things.

    Now time itself arrives at perpetual prosperity,
    And manifold blessings descend anew.
    Though this servant, fortunate to meet this age of glory,
    Undeserving of such favor, remains distant,
    Unable to hurry forth in the palace halls,
    Yet my heart follows the ancient way of sage-kings,
    And multiplies its songs of praise and blessing.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Bear's handle (Dipper) returning to the east marks the beginning of spring and the new year in traditional East Asian cosmology.
  - key: ''
    value: Phoenix Calendar (鳳曆) refers to an auspicious calendar, with the phoenix symbolizing imperial renewal.
  - key: ''
    value: The pepper wine cup (椒觴) is a ceremonial vessel used in court festivities to celebrate auspicious occasions.
  - key: ''
    value: Dragon-steps (龍墀) refers to the imperial palace, where only the ruler may tread.
  - key: ''
    value: This memorial follows the formal conventions of court congratulatory addresses, with the author expressing both loyalty and the philosophical ideals of harmonious governance.
